categories.summary: The buyer mentions that they no longer need imurica to pull LinkedIn data for them, as their internal team can handle it themselves. They are also phasing out Twitter.

The buyer raises several concerns regarding the service. First, they need the report in PowerPoint format. Second, they no longer require LinkedIn data pulling. Third, they are phasing out Twitter. Fourth, they point out that the same story is sometimes replicated across different publications. Finally, they want to review the search terms used for the industry news section to ensure they align with their priorities.
The buyer expresses confusion and frustration regarding issues with the invoices and the overall process, indicating a lack of understanding of why the process is so messy this time around.
Olivia mentions that they may get feedback from ELT (Executive Leadership Team) or higher up, indicating that decisions could be influenced by senior leadership.

Iona escalated the invoice issue internally and it was approved. The team needs the report in PowerPoint format because they feed stuff in. Aaron and his team can pull LinkedIn data themselves. The three guys may want to add titles to the media list.

summary.text: This sales meeting between Ava Thompson representing the seller side and Emma Roberts and Olivia Wilson from VodafoneThree, focused on reporting and briefing updates. VodafoneThree requested the LinkedIn data pull be discontinued due to internal duplication and confirmed satisfaction with reporting updates pending Teresa's final version incorporating BT and EE data. They discussed the structure of the news summary, agreeing to keep Vodafone and Three coverage under a single "Vodafone Three" section for now, with potential for future separation. VodafoneThree also raised a concern about duplicated stories in the briefing and requested a review of the media list and search terms used for the industry news section to ensure alignment with Three's priorities. The seller, Ava, agreed to resend the media list and industry search terms after the call.

items.original_text: Teresa to send the final version of the report in PowerPoint format, merging the BT and EE data.
Ava to pass on the information that VodafoneThree team will pull their own LinkedIn data internally.
Ava to double-check if Sophia shared the media list with Emma and Olivia. If not, ping it over to them.
Emma and Olivia to review the media list and identify any titles that the Three UK team wants to add.
Ava to confirm the search terms used for the industry news section in the news briefing and share them with Emma and Olivia.
